    "Bias in a language model refers to the systematic inaccuracies or stereotypes in the generated language output, which are influenced by the training data and reflect the societal and cultural prejudices that exist in that data [60].",
    "These biases can affect language models in many ways, such as perpetuating stereotypes, creating misunderstandings, or spreading harmful and false information.In 2016, Microsoft's chatbot, called Tay, rapidly adopted the toxic behavior of the worst online trolls, spreading racist, sexist, and other forms of abuse."
